        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1890-09-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1890-09-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="96" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d96">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Wharton</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Mizner</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1890-09-15">
                            <hi rend="italic">September</hi> 15,
                            1890</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 174.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department has received your No. 147 of
                        the 27th ultimo, in which you repeat the instructions sent you relative to
                        the employment of the, concurrent good offices of the United States and
                        Mexico to bring about peace in Central America.</p>
                <p>The desired peace having already been secured prior to the occurrence of an
                        opportunity to act on those instructions, the telegram of the 19th ultimo,
                        which you quote, is no longer of special pertinence.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">William F. Wharton</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
